  "text": "8. The SMES formulation and parameter values (unless otherwise stated) used in the original papers [11, 15, 16 ] are adopted here. Thus the ideal gas EoS is used to model the confined phase, the bag model EoS is used for the QGP phase, and the first order phase transition between them is assumed. A and B, which are independent of the source number distribution. The measures were referred to as strongly intensive quantities [17] . The first measure of this type was introduced in Ref. [18] and then the concept was generalized [17] and extended to third [19] and higher moments [CITATION_1] . Here the predictions of the SMES model will be calculated for strongly intensive quantities which include the first and second moments of A and B.",
